Tip

When completing a number sentence, the missing number can be referred to in your mind as ‘what number’. This can help you think through the question.

success.question_text: If Perth time is 9 hours ahead of London time, what time is it in Perth?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Time

stimulus_2.text:
A football match commenced in London at 5 pm.

Armena is at home in Perth and is watching the game live on her television.

review_3.column_1_text:
If Perth is 9 hours ahead of London time, you add on 9 hours to 5 pm to get the Perth time.

5 pm plus 7 hours is midnight, and then 2 hours is 2 am.

Armena is watching the game at 2 am in Perth the following day.

success.question_text: What am I?

stimulus_1.text: I am a 3D solid. I have two triangular faces and three rectangular faces.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

A triangular prism has five faces, nine edges and six vertices (corners). For any solid the number of faces plus the number of vertices is always two more than the number of edges.

success.question_text: What is the best estimate for the mass of one two-dollar coin?

stimulus_1.text: Herman uses a glass jar as a piggy bank for his loose change.

stimulus_3.text:
When it contains 100 two-dollar coins it has a mass of 1 kg.

When the jar is empty, it has a mass of 300 g.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Use the conversion 1000 grams (g) = 1 kilogram (kg). To change grams to kilograms, divide by 1000. To change kilograms to grams, multiply by 1000.

success.question_text: What is the missing number?
Which is the latest train that Edward can catch from Redhill so that he arrives at least five minutes early?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Tables

stimulus_2.text: Edward has an appointment in the city at twenty to ten. It will take him eight minutes to walk from the station and he wants to be five minutes early.

review_3.column_1_text:
Twenty to ten is 9:40.

Edward needs to be at the city station (8 + 5) minutes = 13 minutes before 9:40.

13 minutes before 9:40 is 9:27.

So Edward will need to catch the train that reaches the city at 9:13.

This train leaves Redhill at 8:50.

Tip

Practise reading bus and train timetables.

success.question_text: If the return journey takes exactly the same time as the forward journey, at what time will Ming arrive back in Ashby?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Tables

stimulus_2.text: Ming catches the train at Ashby at 8:43 and travels to Pottsville. She spends exactly one and a half hours in Pottsville and then catches a train back to Ashby.

review_3.column_1_text:
The 8:43 train from Ashby arrives in Pottsville at 9:02. The journey takes 19 minutes (17 minutes from 8:43 until 9:00 and 2 minutes more).

Ming will be in Pottsville one and a half hours, until 10:32. The return journey will also take 19 minutes.

Time of return = 10:51.

 

Tip

Take care when adding times. Remember there are 60 minutes in an hour so a time such as 8:43 is not a decimal.

success.question_text: Which statement is not correct?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Tables

review_3.column_1_text:
Consider each option:

  • ‘The trip from Jennings to the city takes 18 minutes.’ Calculate the time for each train to travel from Jennings to the city. It is always 18 minutes. This option is correct.
  • ‘The 9:30 from Featherstone takes the shortest time to reach the city.’ The 9:30 from Featherstone takes 36 minutes to reach the city. The 9:10 from Featherstone takes 37 minutes and the other trains take 38 minutes to reach the city. This option is correct.
  • ‘The longest time between stops is 8 minutes.’ The first three trains take 8 minutes to travel from Featherstone to Ashby. This is the longest time of any train between stops. This option is correct.
  • ‘Trains leave Featherstone at 15 minute intervals.’ There are 15 minutes between the first and second train leaving Featherstone and also between the second and third train but there are 20 minutes between the 3rd and 4th trains and 20 minutes between the 4th and 5th trains. This option is not correct.

review_4.column_1_text:
The statement that is not correct is ‘Trains leave Featherstone at 15-minute intervals.’

Tip

You only need to find one contradiction to prove something wrong.

choice_1.label: The trip from Jennings to the city takes 18 minutes.

choice_2.label: The 9:30 from Featherstone takes the shortest time to reach the city.

choice_3.label: The longest time between stops is 8 minutes.

success.question_text: Which square will not be shaded when the design is complete?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

A symmetrical design might have line symmetry or rotational symmetry. If it has line symmetry then the design could be folded along a line (the axis of symmetry) and the two halves would match exactly. If it has rotational symmetry the design could be turned about its centre through a number of degrees so that the resulting image is exactly the same as the original.

success.question_text:
Leonie lives in Cobar and plans a short walk at 14:00.

What is the UV Index during her walk?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Graphs

stimulus_1.text: The forecast graphs show the (Ultra-violet) UV index for two locations.

review_3.column_1_text:
The time 14:00 is the same as 2:00 pm.

On the graph for Cobar, the UV Index is showing a red colour which means Very High.

Tip

Always read carefully the labels of a graph so that you understand what information has been incorporated in the graph.

success.question_text: How much longer is the UV Alert in Cobar than in Adelaide?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Graphs

stimulus_1.text: The forecast graphs show the (Ultra-violet) UV index for two locations.

review_3.column_1_text:
The UV alert is written at the top of each graph.

In Cobar the UV Alert starts at 9:50 am while in Adelaide it starts at 10:00 am. The Cobar alert starts 10 minutes earlier.

In Adelaide the UV alert finishes at 4:50 pm while in Cobar it finishes at 5:10 pm. The Cobar alert finishes 20 minutes later.

Now 10 min + 20 min = 30 min

The Cobar alert lasts 30 minutes longer.

Tip

Always read carefully the labels of a graph so that you understand what information has been incorporated in the graph.

success.question_text: What is the area of the rectangle?

stimulus_1.text: A rectangle encloses two circles which each have a radius of 4 cm.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A radius is the distance from the centre of a circle to the outside (circumference). The diameter is a line from one side of a circle to the other which passes through the centre. The radius is half the diameter.

success.question_text: Which is not a step in this pattern?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Number Patterns

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

Examining each of the steps you can see that the first number is one more than the step number, the 2nd number is one less than the step number and the final number is the square of the step number (the step number multiplied by itself).

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Look carefully at all parts of a pattern. Every part must obey whatever rule applies.

success.question_text: What will be the tenth figure?

stimulus_1.text: The first eight figures in a pattern of rotations are shown below.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A rotation of 90 degrees in a clockwise direction produces a different result to a rotation of 90 degrees in an anticlockwise direction. A rotation of 180 degrees in either a clockwise or anticlockwise direction will produce the same result.
